    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Sheet metal seams having a bottom plate with a turned edge that overlaps the side plate; the seam may be secured by welding, soldering, or riveting at the overlapping joint. An example of a lap bottom seam is the seam of the bottom of a tin or steel can.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
